subject: Re: [junit] Problems with assertEquals...
msgSnippet: Sometimes when the two objects have been loaded by two different classloader-s the interpreter does not recognize them as equal. Their values are the same but
messageBody:
Sometimes when the two objects have been loaded by two different classloader-s the interpreter does not recognize them as equal. Their values are the same but their identity in the virtual machine differ.

See some info about Classloaders and classloading.

Regards
Vera
